HEADWORD: Contrivable
<hw>Con*triv"a*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Capable of
being contrived, planned, invented, or devised.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A perpetual motion may seem easily <qex>contrivable</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Bp. Wilkins.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Contrivance</ent>⟦br⟧
